The paper discusses machine translation evaluation, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes novel evaluation methods that utilize augmented factors and tunable models, which suggests the involvement of artificial intelligence (AI) and machine learning (ML) techniques, making cs.AI and cs.LG likely sub-categories as well. The paper also mentions the use of linguistic features and factors, which could relate to information retrieval (IR) and computer vision (CV), making them less likely but still possible sub-categories.
